{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":78800,"duration_api_ms":120792,"num_turns":5,"result":"","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"6c562313-c0ec-4ac5-b1fd-987c06ec27a6","total_cost_usd":0.36981325,"usage":{"input_tokens":4,"cache_creation_input_tokens":25474,"cache_read_input_tokens":77785,"output_tokens":2499,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":25474,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"},"modelUsage":{"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001":{"inputTokens":106,"outputTokens":6189,"cacheReadInputTokens":313635,"cacheCreationInputTokens":37439,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.10921325,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":32000},"claude-opus-4-6":{"inputTokens":4,"outputTokens":2499,"cacheReadInputTokens":77785,"cacheCreationInputTokens":25474,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.2606,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":64000}},"permission_denials":[],"structured_output":{"summary":"All three amendments are substantiated by the code. The concurrency test has a real synchronization gap where thread 2 may not be scheduled before the 100ms timeout. The FnOnce clone issue is confirmed but low-impact. The retry-progress aggregation bug is a genuine correctness defect where retries create duplicate bead counts in MilestoneProgress.","votes":[{"amendment_id":"fr-7-8c8af466","decision":"accept","rationale":"Verified in service.rs:2339-2363. Thread 2 is spawned and then immediately checked with recv_timeout(Duration::from_millis(100)). There is no synchronization barrier confirming thread 2 has reached the write lock contention point before the timeout assertion. Under CI load, thread 2 may not even be scheduled within 100ms, so the assertion passes vacuously — it proves nothing about lock serialization. Thread 1 correctly uses entered_tx/entered_rx to confirm it reached the blocking point, but thread 2 lacks an equivalent signal. Adding a pre-lock channel send from thread 2 would make the test deterministic."},{"amendment_id":"fr-7-0047ba65","decision":"accept","rationale":"Confirmed that both closures passed to with_milestone_write_lock are FnOnce, and plan_hash.clone() (persist_plan) and outcome_detail.clone() (update_task_run) each allocate a new String unnecessarily. Since the closure runs exactly once, the owned values could be moved in and consumed directly. This is a minor inefficiency — one String allocation per call — but it is a valid and straightforward improvement that also clarifies ownership semantics. Low priority but correct."},{"amendment_id":"fr-7-368e3c97","decision":"accept","rationale":"Verified in model.rs and service.rs. collapse_task_run_attempts uses same_attempt() which matches entries by run_id or started_at timestamp — it only merges a legacy start row with its corresponding terminal row for the same attempt. Separate retries of the same bead (different run_ids, different timestamps) survive as distinct terminal rows. The reconcile logic in service.rs then counts each terminal outcome independently: a bead that failed in run-1 and succeeded in run-2 will increment both failed_beads and completed_beads. This contradicts the documented semantics of MilestoneProgress as bead counts (not attempt counts) and makes status.json reflect cumulative attempt history rather than current per-bead state. The fix should deduplicate to one current state per bead before counting."}]},"fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"785445db-5e1d-4f61-8f81-c5e2335d7584"}
